        Parameters:
        object - The metadata to copy values from, or null if none.
        See Also:
        castOrCopy(Identification)

    • Method Detail

      • castOrCopy

        public static AbstractIdentification castOrCopy(Identification object)
        Returns a SIS metadata implementation with the values of the given arbitrary implementation. This method performs the first applicable action in the following choices:
        • If the given object is null, then this method returns null.
        • Otherwise if the given object is is an instance of DataIdentification or ServiceIdentification, then this method delegates to the castOrCopy(…) method of the corresponding SIS subclass. Note that if the given object implements more than one of the above-cited interfaces, then the castOrCopy(…) method to be used is unspecified.
        • Otherwise if the given object is already an instance of AbstractIdentification, then it is returned unchanged.
        • Otherwise a new AbstractIdentification instance is created using the copy constructor and returned. Note that this is a shallow copy operation, since the other metadata contained in the given object are not recursively copied.
        Parameters:
        object - The object to get as a SIS implementation, or null if none.
        Returns:
        A SIS implementation containing the values of the given object (may be the given object itself), or null if the argument was null.
